reviews.review: great mystery, big twists, and hilarious!

Excellent murder mystery comedy. Great cast, great acting, amazing story line. It is so much fun to watch and witness the web unravel. Also political and current to today's 1%, supremacist and racial issues. I can't say enough good things about this film.

A wonderful murder mystery whodunit with a great plot which has plenty of good twists and turns that will keep you guessing right up until the end.  The writing is funny and quirky, the acting and cast performances are great, and although it does labour the explanation phase a bit, it's a marvelous production overall.

‪#KnivesOut is a well-made work of art with an excellent cast (including performances by Daniel Craig, Chris Evans, Ana de Armas, Lakeith Steinfeld, Jamie Lee Curtis, Christopher Plummer and Toni Collette), a well-paced runtime and a story of a mystery that'll leave you thinking you know the answer until the very end shocks you.‬ I really hope it gets enough attention to score some Oscar nominations.

‪This movie only proves that Rian Johnson should still get to make his Star Wars trilogy at Disney‬ and I hope he does.

Final rating: 5 stars out of 5 stars. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

One of the most entertaining movies of the year. Excellent pacing keeps the movie moving along. Just enough clues along the way that you don't feel cheated at each twist and turn nor the final reveal and conclusion. Every performance is engaging and brings characters to life. Plenty of subtle humor and good pacing keep the film from feeling its 130-minute run time.
